f positive, the receiver will try to maintain the preferred height and the aspect ratio for the finder by dynamically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changing the inset. If negative this property will be ignored.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Defaults to -1;","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://net.doo.ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK/documentation/ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK":{"title":"ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Version: 8.0.1"}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotdocumentscannersdk"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK/documentation/ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotdocumentscannersdk\/sbsdkbasescannerviewfinderconfiguration","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","title":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","abstract":[{"text":"The view finder configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed.","type":"text"